snippet.textDisplay:
For anyone who lives in the UK and is scared of social media censorship, consider downloading Tor.


If you don't live in a place where the internet is censored, consider installing Snowflake (an extension that helps the Tor network work better), setting up a Tor relay, or donating to Tor. I'm not going to post links because I don't want to get flagged as spam, but using DuckDuckGo should help you find what you want.

Streaming laws and rites need to be created, Blizzard can't have it both ways, if you as a publisher sells a game on steam that should be part of the terms of service, a consumer has the rite to stream their game on any streaming service, wether thats invidia or steam or any other streaming company or even host your own streaming service on a server somewhere where your game is installed on.
